  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6592.58 sitting right between the max negative gamma wall at 6590 (-39B) and max positive at 6605 (+26B), dealers are caught in a critical hedging zone where they must buy this dip aggressively as spot hovers near the largest amplifying level. The massive 23.5% GEX surge indicates fresh positioning that's creating violent hedging flows, and with dealers short gamma in BREAKOUT regime, any move below 6590 will trigger accelerated selling while a push above 6605 faces heavy dealer supply. Watch 6590 as the key inflection—break below and expect cascading selling toward the 6580/6585 amplifying walls, while reclaim of 6605 could spark momentum higher as dealers flip from buying to selling.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect explosive moves in either direction from this tight range between 6590-6605.",
